Html:
Sure can, it can be hosted inside of a windows forms host. You will have to make reference to Crystal Reports (obviously) and WindowsFormsIntegration in your project.<br />
<br />
In the XAML heading use<br />
<pre><code>xmlns:cr=&quot;clr-namespace:CrystalDecisions.Windows.Forms;assembly=CrystalDecisions.Windows.Forms&quot;
</code></pre>

and in your XAML body use<br />
<pre><code> &lt;WindowsFormsHost&gt;
         &lt;cr:CrystalReportViewer x:Name=&quot;crCrystalReportViewer&quot; /&gt;
 &lt;/WindowsFormsHost&gt;</code></pre>
